"{\"uid\": \"nbcwashington.com-paris-2024-summer-olympics-noah-lyles-taken-off-track-in-wheelchair-moments-after-winning-bronze-at-paris-olympics-3689224\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"U.S. sprinter Noah Lyles was unable to compete the Olympic double, but did earn a bronze in the men's 200m for the second straight Olympic Games.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 145, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 14, \"end\": 24, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Noah Lyles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Lyles, who has asthma, ran the race despite testing positive for COVID-19 on Tuesday.\", \"from\": 146, \"to\": 231, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 211, \"end\": 219, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/COVID-19\", \"score\": 0.9999956295998805, \"rank\": 4.3446330782225924e-06, \"text\": \"COVID-19\", \"types\": [\"Q12136\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/COVID-19\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/COVID-19\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Noah Lylessaid he wasdiagnosed with COVID-19days before winning bronze in the men's 200m at the Paris Olympics.\", \"from\": 233, \"to\": 344, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Moments after finishing third in the race, Lyles left the track in a wheelchair with medical staff, then returned to speak on live TV.\", \"from\": 345, \"to\": 479, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 388, \"end\": 393, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trey_Lyles\", \"score\": 0.9796927234929395, \"rank\": 0.02072811710051569, \"text\": \"Lyles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trey_Lyles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trey_Lyles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Alexandria, Virginia, athleteran the 200m with a time of 19.70 on Thursday, then lay down on the ground.\", \"from\": 481, \"to\": 589, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 497, \"end\": 505, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Virginia\", \"score\": 0.9581713823601237, \"rank\": 0.03667922965760738, \"text\": \"Virginia\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Virginia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Virginia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He continued sitting while medical attendants brought him water.\", \"from\": 590, \"to\": 654, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A short time later, he left the track in a wheelchair.\", \"from\": 655, \"to\": 709, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Stream NBC4 newscasts for free right here, right now.\", \"from\": 711, \"to\": 764, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's taken its toll for sure, but I have never been more proud of myself for being able to come out here and get a bronze medal,\\\" Lyles later said.\", \"from\": 766, \"to\": 914, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Last Olympics I was very disappointed and this time I could not be more proud.\\\"\", \"from\": 915, \"to\": 995, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"USA Track & Field confirmed that Lyles tested positive for COVID-19, and said the organization \\\"swiftly enacted all necessary protocols to prioritize his health, the wellbeing of our team, and the safety of fellow competitors.\\\"\", \"from\": 997, \"to\": 1224, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1030, \"end\": 1035, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trey_Lyles\", \"score\": 0.9796927234929395, \"rank\": 0.02072811710051569, \"text\": \"Lyles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trey_Lyles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trey_Lyles\"}, {\"begin\": 1056, \"end\": 1064, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/COVID-19\", \"score\": 0.9999956295998805, \"rank\": 4.3446330782225924e-06, \"text\": \"COVID-19\", \"types\": [\"Q12136\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/COVID-19\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/COVID-19\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I have run with worse conditions,\\\" Lyles later said.\", \"from\": 1226, \"to\": 1279, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Fans were concerned and confused as Lyles took many deep breaths following the race.\", \"from\": 1281, \"to\": 1365, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1317, \"end\": 1322, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trey_Lyles\", \"score\": 0.9796927234929395, \"rank\": 0.02072811710051569, \"text\": \"Lyles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trey_Lyles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trey_Lyles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Lyles' mother first shared news of the COVID diagnosis, NBC's Lewis Johnson reported on the track broadcast.\", \"from\": 1367, \"to\": 1475, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1423, \"end\": 1426, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\", \"score\": 0.9999598148429371, \"rank\": 3.6679081723643754e-05, \"text\": \"NBC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\"}, {\"begin\": 1429, \"end\": 1442, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lewis_Johnson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Lewis Johnson\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lewis_Johnson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lewis_Johnson\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I ran into his mom Keisha Caine Bishop who was distraught trying to find him as well,\\\" Johnson said.\", \"from\": 1477, \"to\": 1578, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1497, \"end\": 1503, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keisha_Buchanan\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Keisha\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keisha_Buchanan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keisha_Buchanan\"}, {\"begin\": 1510, \"end\": 1516, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bishop\", \"score\": 0.9998548915143949, \"rank\": 0.00012013291604643292, \"text\": \"Bishop\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bishop\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bishop\"}, {\"begin\": 1565, \"end\": 1572, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lyndon_B._Johnson\", \"score\": 0.980983969926511, \"rank\": 0.019379729095683963, \"text\": \"Johnson\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lyndon_B._Johnson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lyndon_B._Johnson\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We found Noah Lyles in medical, they are being tended to and she did confirm that Noah had been diagnosed with COVID two days ago.\\\"\", \"from\": 1579, \"to\": 1711, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1589, \"end\": 1599, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Noah Lyles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\"}, {\"begin\": 1662, \"end\": 1666, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Luke_Snyder_and_Noah_Mayer\", \"score\": 0.9644893630904174, \"rank\": 0.03677927556733311, \"text\": \"Noah\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Luke_Snyder_and_Noah_Mayer\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Luke_Snyder_and_Noah_Mayer\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Several minutes later, Lyles came out and spoke to Johnson during his broadcast and said he started feeling sick a couple of days after winning a gold medal in the 100m race.\", \"from\": 1713, \"to\": 1887, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1736, \"end\": 1741, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trey_Lyles\", \"score\": 0.9796927234929395, \"rank\": 0.02072811710051569, \"text\": \"Lyles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trey_Lyles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trey_Lyles\"}, {\"begin\": 1764, \"end\": 1771, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lyndon_B._Johnson\", \"score\": 0.980983969926511, \"rank\": 0.019379729095683963, \"text\": \"Johnson\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lyndon_B._Johnson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lyndon_B._Johnson\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Yeah I woke up early, about 5 a.m. on Tuesday morning and I just was feeling really horrible.\", \"from\": 1889, \"to\": 1983, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I knew it was more than just being sore from the [100m race].\", \"from\": 1984, \"to\": 2045, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Woke up the doctors, and we tested, and unfortunately, it came up that I was positive for COVID.\", \"from\": 2046, \"to\": 2142, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"My first thought was not to panic, thinking, I have been in worse situations, I have run with worse conditions,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 2143, \"to\": 2264, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Lyles previously said he has asthma, whichthe CDC has saidcan put people \\\"at increased risk for getting very sick from COVID-19.\\\"\", \"from\": 2268, \"to\": 2397, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2314, \"end\": 2317, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Centers_for_Disease_Control_and_Prevention\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.85419963254186e-22, \"text\": \"CDC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q327333\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Centers_for_Disease_Control_and_Prevention\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Centers_for_Disease_Control_and_Prevention\"}, {\"begin\": 2387, \"end\": 2395, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/COVID-19\", \"score\": 0.9999956295998805, \"rank\": 4.3446330782225924e-06, \"text\": \"COVID-19\", \"types\": [\"Q12136\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/COVID-19\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/COVID-19\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Lyles won gold in the 100m race on Sunday,taking the crown as \\\"fastest man in the world\\\" following a dramatic photo finish.He had been open about trying to win gold in both the 200m and 100m races.\", \"from\": 2399, \"to\": 2596, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"While the 200m is typically his best event, Lyles wasn't in peak shape while battling COVID.\", \"from\": 2597, \"to\": 2689, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2641, \"end\": 2646, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trey_Lyles\", \"score\": 0.9796927234929395, \"rank\": 0.02072811710051569, \"text\": \"Lyles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trey_Lyles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trey_Lyles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Noah Lyles provides an update on his condition after the 200m final.#ParisOlympics\\ud83d\\udcfa NBC & Peacockpic.twitter.com/9Qs1vcBycf  USA Track & Field said it was Lyles' choice to compete after he tested positive on Monday.\", \"from\": 2691, \"to\": 2906, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2691, \"end\": 2701, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Noah Lyles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\"}, {\"begin\": 2847, \"end\": 2852, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trey_Lyles\", \"score\": 0.9796927234929395, \"rank\": 0.02072811710051569, \"text\": \"Lyles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trey_Lyles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trey_Lyles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Our primary commitment is to ensure the safety of Team USA athletes while upholding their right to compete.\", \"from\": 2908, \"to\": 3016, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2960, \"end\": 2968, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9143438879606176, \"rank\": 0.07653007804212486, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"After a thorough medical evaluation, Noah chose to compete tonight.\", \"from\": 3017, \"to\": 3084, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3055, \"end\": 3059, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Luke_Snyder_and_Noah_Mayer\", \"score\": 0.9644893630904174, \"rank\": 0.03677927556733311, \"text\": \"Noah\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Luke_Snyder_and_Noah_Mayer\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Luke_Snyder_and_Noah_Mayer\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We respect his decision and will continue to monitor his condition closely,\\\" the statement said.\", \"from\": 3085, \"to\": 3181, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"As an organization, we are rigorously adhering to CDC, USOPC, and IOC guidelines for respiratory illnesses to prevent the spread of illness among team members, safeguarding their health and performance,\\\" USA Track & Field said.\", \"from\": 3183, \"to\": 3411, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3235, \"end\": 3238, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Centers_for_Disease_Control_and_Prevention\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.85419963254186e-22, \"text\": \"CDC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q327333\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Centers_for_Disease_Control_and_Prevention\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Centers_for_Disease_Control_and_Prevention\"}]}]}"